'''''tinco''''' is a noun meaning "metal" in [[Quenya]].<ref name="Names">{{App|Letters}}, Note, ''The names of the letters''</ref>

 [[Image:Tinco.gif|left]]''Tinco'' is also the name in Quenya of the first letter of the [[Tengwar]] alphabet.<ref name="Names"/>  It is the first letter of the first grade or [[Tyellë]], which contains "voiceless stops" and it is the first letter in the dental or ''t''-series of consonants, the ''[[Tincotéma]]''.  In all modes ''Tinco'' represents '''T'''.<ref>{{App|Letters}}</ref>  The Westron name for this letter is '''''Tó'''''.<ref>See ''[[Alphabet of Fëanor: Numenian, or Westron, Mode]]''</ref>


==Etymology==
The word derives from the [[Primitive Quendian]] [[Sundocarme|root]] [[TINKŌ]].<ref>{{LR|Etymologies}}, TINKŌ -</ref>
